Description: Bridge KSystemClipboard <-> KRdp::Clipboard for --plasma sessions.
 .
 ``PortalSession`` already wires Wayland's system clipboard to the
 RDP CLIPRDR channel through ``KSystemClipboard`` (see
 ``src/PortalSession.cpp`` lines ~99-119 and ``setClipboardData``
 around line 219). The corresponding ``PlasmaScreencastV1Session``
 was left with a stub ``setClipboardData`` and no
 ``KSystemClipboard::changed`` listener, so when krdpserver runs in
 ``--plasma`` mode (the only mode that works on a TTY-Plasma
 session because xdg-desktop-portal-kde refuses to authorise an
 RDP screen-cast against a service that isn't a graphical app),
 clipboard sync between the host and the RDP client is silently
 dropped:
 .
   * Copying anything in the Plasma session does not reach mstsc.
   * Copying from inside mstsc does not reach the Plasma session.
 .
 The fix is to mirror PortalSession's logic in the Plasma session
 class. ``KSystemClipboard`` (from KGuiAddons, already linked into
 KRdp via ``KF6::GuiAddons`` -- see ``src/CMakeLists.txt``) exposes
 the system selection over ``zwlr_data_control_v1`` /
 ``ext_data_control_v1`` even when our QGuiApplication has no
 surface focus, which is required because krdpserver runs in the
 background of the seat's Plasma session and never owns a window.
 .
 Implementation notes:
 .
   * The KSystemClipboard handler clones the returned QMimeData
     before emitting ``clipboardDataChanged``, identically to the
     portal path. KSystemClipboard explicitly retains ownership of
     the QMimeData it returns from ``mimeData()``, while the
     Clipboard receiver calls ``delete d->serverData`` on the
     pointer it stores -- emitting the original would lead to a
     double-free.
   * ``setClipboardData(nullptr)`` is treated as "clear the system
     clipboard", consistent with PortalSession.
   * ``QClipboard::Clipboard`` is used as the mode (not
     ``QClipboard::Selection``) because RDP's CLIPRDR channel maps
     to the Windows-style explicit clipboard, not the X11 primary
     selection.
 .
 No new dependencies are introduced: KGuiAddons is already a
 PUBLIC link dependency of the KRdp library and ``<KSystemClipboard>``
 / ``<QMimeData>`` headers are already available in the include path
 used by PortalSession.cpp.
Author: ConsoleRDP <consolerdp@local>
Forwarded: not-yet
Last-Update: 2026-05-01
